sec.p:
A typical metabolite identification approach involves the following steps:
predict possible metabolites using in silico methods (see Section 3.1) or based on researcher’s experience;
apply survey scans of the test and control samples;
compare ion chromatograms of the test and control samples to determine the m/z values of expected and unexpected metabolites;
conduct product ion scan and/or MS/MS; MSn on the m/z of suspected metabolites and propose metabolite structures;
